# Context window closeout

**Triggers:** `close out thread` · `closeout thread` · `close this thread` · `end thread` · `context closeout` · `wrap this chat` · `thread handoff`

When the user uses any trigger above, or the chat is too long/noisy to continue:

1. Read [`docs/SOP/CONTEXT_WINDOW_CLOSEOUT_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/CONTEXT_WINDOW_CLOSEOUT_V1.md).
2. Run `context_window_closeout.cmd --sweep --whats-next "<one-line next action>"` (gate+commit+push, then record). Use `add-build` / `add-human` when sweep parks items.
3. Complete `<!-- AGENT_FILL -->` sections in draft only when narrative/triage needs capture.
4. End with **AGENT CONTINUITY** block (`safe_to_switch` comes from sweep when `--sweep` ran).

**Not** chapter closeout (`apply_control_closeout_v1`) unless a relay closeout slice is also in scope.

**Next thread:** user asks `what's next?` — agent **auto-executes** operator verdict per `ppe-unified-run.mdc` (read `WHATS_NEXT.md` + `AGENT_CONTINUITY_BRIEF.md` for context; no @ required).
